    </div>
    <div class="places">
        <div>
            <h3>Paris</h3>
            <img src="../pictures/pexels-jarod-17185651.jpg" alt="Paris">
            <p><span>Paris, France's capital, is a major European city and a global center for art, fashion, gastronomy, and culture. Its 19th-century cityscape is crisscrossed by wide boulevards and the River Seine. Beyond such landmarks as the Eiffel Tower and the 12th-century Gothic Notre-Dame cathedral, the city is known for its cafe culture and designer boutiques along the Rue du Faubourg Saint-Honoré.</span></p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h3>Switzerland</h3>
            <img src="../pictures/pexels-ozrenildo-1291766.jpg" alt="Switzerland">
            <p><span>Switzerland is a dream destination known for its stunning landscapes, serene lakes, and majestic snow-capped mountains. Famous for the Swiss Alps, Switzerland offers a perfect blend of natural beauty and modern urban charm, making it a year-round travel hotspot. Whether you’re a nature enthusiast, an adventure seeker, or simply looking for a peaceful retreat, Switzerland has something for everyone.</span></p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h3>Goa</h3>
            <img src="../pictures/pexels-sethu-gauri-shankar-362019-978667.jpg" alt="Goa">
            <p><span>Goa is India’s ultimate beach destination, famed for its golden sandy shores, vibrant nightlife, and rich cultural heritage. This small state on the western coast of India blends Portuguese colonial architecture with traditional Indian culture, making it a unique and fascinating place to explore. Goa is ideal for beach lovers, adventure enthusiasts, and history buffs alike, offering a wide range of activities from water sports to historical sightseeing.</span></p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h3>Egypt</h3>
            <img src="../pictures/pexels-marcel-winger-1281376-2445852.jpg" alt="Egypt">
            <p><span>Egypt is a land of ancient wonders, where history, culture, and mystery come alive. Known as the "Cradle of Civilization," Egypt boasts some of the most iconic historical landmarks in the world, including the majestic Pyramids of Giza, the Sphinx, and the timeless Nile River. This North African country offers a captivating blend of archaeological marvels, rich cultural traditions, and stunning desert landscapes.</span></p>
